main event: An unidentified flying object sighting occurred on 11 November 1956 in Salineville, Ohio, involving bright light objects.
interesting points: The sighting lasted several minutes,Two objects were observed that appeared larger than stars,The objects were seen at very high altitudes,One of the conclusions suggested that the sighting was probably caused by an aircraft or balloon,There were no photographs included in the report.
sighted object: two bright light objects in the sky
